The location also benefits from excellent transport links, including Manor Park mainline, Wanstead tube station and the much anticipated Cross-Rail due to open in in 2019. Located in the heart of the Conservation Area, this property is just a few minutes' walk from the idyllic Wanstead Park, which offers stunning woodland views with its ornamental lakes, country walks and easy access through to Central Wanstead and Wanstead flats offering wide open spaces for runners, dog walkers and children to play. 

To the ground floor there are three good sized reception rooms, including a conservatory overlooking the garden and a good sized, modern kitchen/diner with a range of integrated appliances. The first floor enjoys a large family bathroom, and three bedrooms, two of which are good sized doubles. To the rear there is a spacious garden mainly laid to lawn with a patio area and handy outbuilding to the rear. There is on road permit parking to the front of the property. short_description: The apartment flat comes with an option of a dedicated garage (that you can rent) but also use of a communal garage and has private parking for one car.
full_description:
Property reference number 5724668. To enquire about this property click the "Request Details" button


***Comfortable second-floor apartment for LONG LET in leafy quiet Wanstead***

This wonderfully decorated pristine part furnished apartment (could be fully furnished) boasts a large airy lounge with a central entrance hallway, two large double bedrooms, a stylish bathroom suite with deep bath and hair hose along with towel warmer and dual gas and electric immersion heater with pressure booster pump.

It has double glazing throughout, a modern sleek fully-fitted kitchen with integrated appliances, energy efficient induction hob, electric grill and two ovens, washing machine, tumble dryer, dishwasher, high-speed microwave, kitchen sink macerator, drinking water filter tap and dimmable LED energy efficient lighting throughout. 

All with an abundance of light throughout the apartment that has just been painted neutral white which goes well with the dark parquet flooring and has had the place fully deep cleaned and carpet wet extraction cleaning. 

The apartment has views of the start of Epping forest at rear bedroom and lounge both North West facing to get alot of evening sun and it is close to both Wanstead and Snaresbrook high-streets that has many amenities along with many bars, cafes, restaurants and convenient shopping facilities.

It is more or less equidistant and near to three underground stations (5-10 mins walk away) where travel by Central Line underground tube to Stratford is ~15 mins and Liverpool Street in ~20 mins with many other easy network choices for commuting including and close to the M11 for ease of getting out of the City and A12 for either direction.

The apartment flat comes with an option of a dedicated garage (that you can rent) but also use of a communal garage and has private parking for one car. 

The apartment has a fob or code operated alarm system that can be monitored and mounted safely. 

The block of apartments has CCTV and security entry phone system.  Come have a look.  Please arrange a visit that is either evening or weekend.



* Please quote ref. 5724668 when enquiring about this property.

Mon - Fri 8am - 8pm
Sat, Sun & public holidays 9am - 4pm

This property would suit couples and families.

short_description: The property has been extended including a stunning side return extension now offering a spacious contemporary kitchen/living area with ground floor wc. Two double bedrooms to the first floor

Two double bedrooms to the first floor with a separate study area and first floor fitted bathroom. There is a beautiful loft conversion with a double bedroom and an ensuite shower room AVAILABLE FROM 1ST SEPTEMEBER - UNFURNISHED
 

BEFORE YOU MOVE IN 
SET UP FEE (tenant's share): £354 (inc VAT) 
Includes contract negotiation (amending and agreeing terms) and arranging the tenancy and agreement. 
FULL REFERENCE FEE: £36 (Inc VAT) per tenant. 
Referencing identity, immigration and visa confirmation, financial credit checks, obtaining references from current or previous employers / landlords and any other relevant information to assess affordability. 
GUARANTOR FEE: £120 (inc VAT) per guarantor (if required) 
Covering credit referencing and preparing a Deed of Guarantee as part of the Tenancy Agreement. 
AMENDMENT FEE: £60 (inc VAT) 
Contract negotiation, amending terms and updating your tenancy agreement during your tenancy. 
TENANCY RE-ASSIGNMENT: £300.00 (inc VAT) 
Where a tenant wishes to surrender their tenancy 
RENEWAL FEE (tenant's share): £120 (inc VAT) 12 months contract - £60 (inc VAT) 6 months contract. 
Including contract negotiation, amending and updating terms and arranging a further tenancy and agreement. 

ENDING YOUR TENANCY 
Check out Fee (tenant's share): £90-£195(inc VAT) 
Attending the property to undertake an updated Schedule of Condition based on the original inventory and negotiating the repayment of the security deposit(s). 

OTHER FEES AND CHARGES 
LOST SECURITY ITEMS: £36 (inc VAT) plus item cost 
Obtaining necessary permissions, sourcing providers and travel costs. 
OUT OF HOURS SERVICES: £36 per hour (inc VAT) plus costs incurred. 
Where actions of the tenant results in the agent (or nominated contractor) attending the property, time to remedy the situation is charged at the hourly rate. 
UNPAID RENTS / RETURNED PAYMENTS 
Interest at 9.6%(Inc VAT) above Bank of England Base Rate from date due. 
PROFESSIONAL CLEANING (if required): £80 (inc VAT) per hour - deducted from the security deposit 
Only charged where professional cleaning is necessary to return the property to the same condition as at the start of the tenancy
